==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neuralgia
<hw>Neu*ral"gi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>ney^ron</grk> nerve + <?/ pain. See <er>nerve</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease, the chief symptom of which is a very
acute pain, exacerbating or intermitting, which follows the course of a
nervous branch, extends to its ramifications, and seems therefore to be
seated in the nerve. It seems to be independent of any structural
lesion.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neuralgic</ent>⟦br⟧
